Text: The last week.
We had somehow finished everything we set out as a team for our project.
The only difficulty this week was that Susu had an exam and was out for two days so we rushed to get our presentation done on Wednesday and Thursday evening.
The good this week.
I felt our team did a good job of getting through what we needed to get done.
Everyone in our team was much more confident in being honest with feedback.
I especially saw more of a effort from Tzu-Rara to be a bit more assertive.
Kiki felt like she did not contribute a lot last week because she had an exam, so she worked quite hard on suggesting final touches to our app.
I was relieved to get our presentation done and it was great way to wrap up all the time and effort we put in for our client.
It was also great to hear our client was happy with the work we had done.
Things to improve as a team overall.
Looking back at the project, the main things we could have done better would be being clear on how we would organise our workflow.
This means how we kept track of tasks that needed to be done each week, and when would we do them.
It was difficult to execute as we were unclear a lot of the time on what we were doing.
Things I could have done better over the project.
I could have been a bit more vocal at certain times when discussing what we should do.
I caught myself not speaking up at times but I also realised that not every idea needed to be debated if the idea was good enough.
Working in a team always highlights the fact that other people will see things differently even if we are looking at the same thing.
So I was constantlyÂ having to evaluate whether or not the potential debate was worth the cost of spending more time discussing.
I think for me I decided to be more vocal about ideas I felt very strongly about and held back when I was not to concerned about.
There can be a strong pull of the ego to feel like your ideas are the only way to do things, but that's probably an illusion in most cases.
I am sure my team mates saw some things I could have done better during the project, but I hope they feel I helped the team out in a positive way.
General thoughts.
I felt the whole project was well organised and the expectations of what to do were pretty clear from the start.
A lot of the difficulty came from dealing with the emotions of uncertainty and frustrationÂ that come with working as a team and trying to develop something in a short period of time.
I realised near the end of the project, that the final product itself had a much smaller percentage of the total marks for the course than the final reflective report.
I began to wonder did I push myself to hard to work on the project?
Should I have relaxed a bit more and spent more time working on my report a bit earlier than this week?.
One part of the project that could be improved, would be to have all the documents for each part of the project (e. g final presentation outline) available at the start of the of the project.
This would give everyone plenty of time to be aware of what is expected at each stage of the process.
This is a pretty minor recommendation and I think the whole project was run very well.
There were days I couldn't be bothered doing anything and then almost addicted to scrolling the internet trying to solve problems.
I feel I've found out I really enjoy the problem solving aspect of these projects and enjoy working on the hardest problems that we might have.
I also found I don't really like spending time on things that matter to other people, like where font is placed on a PowerPoint or debating the merits of using one word over another in a sentence.
But I realise the power of team work is that each persons critical eye - unifies to form a much stronger view on reality than one person can hold.
I had one of the best sleeps I've had in 5 weeks on Friday.
Time to recharge and get ready for the next one.
Overall
